    Prior to the [!1 Itascan World War] in 17 P.W., there were eight major independent powers on the surface of Itascus.  These powers were:
        Saryllia, with a population of 300 Million; 
        Amenira, with a population of 270 Million; 
        Corrum, with a population of 240 Million;  
        Amora, with a population of 210 Million; 
        Carria, with a population of 200 Million; 
        Borone, with a population of 170; 
        Queensland, with a population of 120 Million; and 
        Finnia, with a population of 23 Million; 

    Saryllia, Amenira, Carria, Queensland, and Finnia existed on the [!2 Ferika Continent].  Saryllia occupied the Northwest of Ferika, bordering Amenira, which occupied the Northeast.  Both shared a southern border with Queensland, which took up the northern half of the [!2 Ferikan Southern Strait].  On the southern border of Queensland was Carria, which took up the lower half of the strait.  Finally, Finna, the smallest Ferikan nation, was a small, land-locked nation on the border between Saryllia and Amenira.

    On the other half of the planet, on the Kullmi and Aphoterra continents, were Borone, Corrum, and Amora.  Borone occupied the entirety of Aphoterra, bordering Amora to the south over the [!2 Aphokull Land Bridge].  Amora, in turn, took up the eastern half of [!2 Kullmia], with Borone occupying the western half.

